<subsection xml:id="subsec-Multiplying-a-fraction-by-a-mixed-number">
        <title>Multiplying a fraction by a mixed number</title>
        <activity>
            <p>
                <alert>Work in groups</alert>
            </p>
            <p>
                A delivery lorry set off from Kitale town to Kisumu city, 
                the lorry is transporting fresh farm produce, and the distance between Kiatle and Kisumu is <m>80 \frac{1}{5}</m> km.
                The lorry uses <m>\frac{4}{5}</m> litres of fuel per kilometre.
            </p>
            <p>
                How many litres of fuel does the lorry need for the whole journey?
            </p>
            <p>
                Share your work with learners in your class.
            </p>
        </activity>
        <example>
            <statement>
                <p>
                    Work out: <m>\frac{2}{5} \times 1 \frac{3}{7} </m>
                </p>
            </statement>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    <ol marker="a)">
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                First, we convert <m>1 \frac{{\color{blue}3}}{{\color{red}7}}</m> to improper fraction.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <md>
                                    <mrow>1 \frac{{\color{blue}3}}{{\color{red}7}} \amp = \frac{({\color{red}7} \times 1) + {\color{blue}3}}{{\color{red}7}} </mrow>
                                    <mrow></mrow>
                                    <mrow> \amp = \frac{10}{7} </mrow>
                                </md>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Multiply the fractions
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <md>
                                    <mrow>\frac{2}{5} \times \frac{10}{7} \amp = \frac{2 \times 10}{5 \times 7}</mrow>
                                    <mrow> </mrow>
                                    <mrow> \amp = \frac{20}{35} </mrow>
                                </md>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>
                                Simplify the numerator and denominator by dividing through by <m>5.</m>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                <md>
                                    <mrow>\frac{20}{35} \amp = \frac{4}{7}</mrow>
                                    <mrow></mrow>
                                    <mrow> \amp = \frac{4}{7} </mrow>
                                </md>
                            </p>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </example>
